  "Description": "The ME6211 series are highly accurate, low-noise CMOS LDO voltage regulators designed for portable and battery-powered applications. They provide a stable output voltage from an input supply, featuring high power supply ripple rejection (PSRR), low output noise, fast transient response, and low dropout voltage. The series includes variants with an enable (CE) pin for power management and variants where the enable function is internally tied high or low. They are stable with low-ESR ceramic capacitors.",
